ObjectStates.LuaScript:
--[[ Lua code. See documentation: https://api.tabletopsimulator.com/ --]]

--[[ The onLoad event is called after the game save finishes loading. --]]
function onLoad()

    --button
    params = {
        click_function = "click_func",
        function_owner = self,
        label          = "SCAN",
        position       = {0, 1.1, 0},
        rotation       = {0, 0, 0},
        width          = 400,
        height         = 400,
        font_size      = 100,
        color          = {0.5, 0.5, 0.5},
        font_color     = {1, 1, 1},
        tooltip        = "",
    }
    self.createButton(params)

    rescan()
end

function rescan()
    broadcastToAll("ComponentScan: Scanning...",{0.7,0.7,0.7})
    --notebook
    allNotes=getNotebookTabs()

    for i=1,#allNotes do
        if(allNotes[i].title=="ComponentScan")then
            removeNotebookTab(allNotes[i].index)
        end
    end

    --scanning
    txt=""
    obj = getAllObjects()
    for objkey,objval in pairs(obj) do
        if(objval~=self)then

            if(objval.getName()~="")then
                txt=txt..objval.name.."("..objval.getName()..")".."("..objval.guid..")".."\n"
            else
                txt=txt..objval.name.."("..objval.guid..")".."\n"
            end

            for comkey,comval in pairs(objval.getComponents()) do
                txt=txt.."    "..comval.name.."\n"

                for varkey,varval in pairs(comval.getVars()) do
                    txt=txt.."        "..varkey.."                     ("..varval..") ".."\n"
                end

                txt=txt
            end

            txt=txt.."\n"
        end
    end

    --writing
    parameters =
    {
        title = "ComponentScan",
        body = txt,
        color = "Grey"
    }
    Notes.addNotebookTab(parameters)
end
function click_func(obj, color, alt_click)
    rescan()
end
